  "prompt": "How do I book a round trip on Uber such that it is counted as a single ride?",
  "response": "Unfortunately, Uber does not have a direct \"round trip\" booking option like some other transportation services. However, you can create a multi-stop trip within the Uber app to simulate a round trip:\n\n1. Open the Uber app\n2. Enter your initial pickup location\n3. Tap \"Add stop\" \n4. Enter your destination\n5. After your first stop, tap \"Add stop\" again\n6. Enter your original starting point as the return destination\n\nThis approach will:\n- Keep the trip as a single ride\n- Track the entire route as one trip\n- Calculate a single fare for the entire journey\n\nA few things to note:\n- The total fare is based on the entire multi-stop route\n- This works best for shorter, more direct round trips\n- For very complex routes, multiple rides might still be more practical\n\nAlways check the estimated fare before confirming the trip to ensure it meets your expectations.",
